# Development rules

- Stack: Vite, semantic HTML5, modular CSS (no framework), vanilla JavaScript (ES modules),
  GSAP + ScrollTrigger. No React/Next.js. Three.js only if approved in docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md.
- Hosting target: GitHub Pages initially — Vite `base` must be set to the repo name.
- Semantic HTML: header, nav, main, section, article, footer; correct heading hierarchy;
  accessible links and buttons. No lorem ipsum, ever.
- Mobile-first CSS with custom properties from DESIGN_SYSTEM.md. Modular files
  (reset, variables, typography, layout, components, sections, animations, responsive).
- JavaScript: small modules per concern (navigation, animations, hero-visual, utils).
  Progressive enhancement — content must remain accessible without JS where possible.
- GSAP: organize animations in separate functions, use gsap.matchMedia for breakpoints,
  register ScrollTrigger once, clean up listeners, prefer transform/opacity over
  width/height/top/left, support prefers-reduced-motion, no scroll hijacking.
- Keep dependencies minimal. Locally hosted fonts, SVG icons, AVIF/WebP images.
- No horizontal overflow. No layout shift from images/fonts (always set width/height).
